it's getting easier but it is still bad for those of you who have ever lost a parent when does it get to where you don't cry everyday i lost my father in january after he suffered a pulmanary embolism he had just left a doctors appt and died in the car in front of the er leaving the parking lot i always thought i was a strong person but my life has fallin apart i cry everyday not all day and i am so mad when will this stop and when will i be able to remember with out falling apart any suggestions it takes a lot of time and how much depends on how close you were to the person with a father it could take a long time it doesn't mean that you're crazy it just means that you loved him very much and you miss him as time goes on though you'll still think about him and the sadness will be there but the anger will be gone after a while you'll smile when you think about him and remember all sorts of good things my youngest sister died two years ago and we were very very close and i'm still not over it i never will be but now when i think about her and talk about her i remember all the good things and the times before she got sick i think that will happen for you too i'm so sorry for your loss Pitaten Kodocha Social rule Father's Day (Doctor Who) Pip (South Park episode) Theory of conduct Le Malade imaginaire Jon Secada The Marshall Mathers LP Cliff Richard Year of the Spider Piccolo Junior Saga Similarities between the Bible and the Qur'an About a Boy Chicago Cubs Miss Saigon The Grim Adventures of Billy and Mandy Scenes from a Memory Hiberno-English Shaggy dog story Wild at Heart (Buffy episode) Charmed The nature of God in Western theology Episodes of Lost (Season 1) Friends Kimi Finster The Ashlee Simpson Show One Tree Hill (TV series) K' Laguna Loire Phoebe Halliwell The Amber Spyglass She Loves You The Shining (film) The Lovely Bones Milton H. Erickson Zhao Yun Grandview, U.S.A. Theodicy EastEnders AFI 100 Years series Invader Zim Humphrey Bogart Random Harvest Harry Pot